tool.name: GDVSpectra_Threshold

param.name: in_nc_file
param.dialogReference: A GDV Likelihood NetCDF generated by the GDV Likelihood tool. Requires x, y dimensions and likelihood ("like") variable.

param.name: out_nc_file
param.dialogReference: The folder location and filename of the output NetCDF file containing GDV Threshold output.

param.name: in_aggregate
param.dialogReference:
Combine all annual data within the input GDV likelihood NetCDF when thresholding. This is recommended to reduce inter-annual seasonal fluctuation.

If not selected, choose a specific year to threshold.

param.name: in_specific_years
param.dialogReference: Select a specific year within the input GDV likelihood NetCDF to threshold.

param.name: in_type
param.dialogReference:
Select the type of thresholding technique to use:

- Standard Deviation: use standard deviation of GDV likelihood data to threshold

- Occurrence Points: use existing GDV species point locations with presence and absence values to threshold via AUC metric

param.name: in_std_dev
param.dialogReference: The standard deviation value to threshold GDV likelihood input. Values where standard deviation is >= to this value will be included (i.e., very high GDV likelihood likelihood), whereas all others will be excluded (i.e., set to NoData).

param.name: in_occurrence_feat
param.dialogReference:
A feature layer or shapefile of points representing known GDV species locations (i.e., occurrences). It is recommended all point should represent one particular GDV species. Points are used to calculate the model accuracy metric known as the Area Under the Curve (AUC). For the AUC, a optimal threshold value is deduced and used to perform the threshold.

Note: the input must be projected in GDA 94 Australian Albers (EPSG: 3577).

param.name: in_pa_column
param.displayname: Field with presence and absence labels
param.dialogReference:
The column that holds a value representing GDV species presence (i.e., 1) and absence (i.e., 0) for each point.

Note: only a integer field containing values 1 and 0 is accepted.

param.name: in_remove_stray
param.dialogReference: Whether to remove salt and pepper (i.e., stray) pixels using a majority filter. For example, if one GDV Likelihood pixel is surrounded by a majority of NoData values, the pixel will be set to NoData.

param.name: in_convert_binary
param.dialogReference: Whether to convert the GDV threshold output to binary (i.e., pixels will have a value of 1 for presence, NoData for absence) or to keep the original likelihood values within the threshold mask area.

param.name: in_add_result_to_map
param.dialogReference: Whether to visualise the results to the currently active map once the process is complete or not.

tool.summary:
Takes a groundwater dependent vegetation (GDV) likelihood map generated from the GDV Likelihood module and thresholds it into a map of high probability only. Thresholding can be performed based on existing presence and absence points of GDV species or via a standard deviation value. The output is a NetCDF file containing the thresholded GDV Likelihood map for either a single year or for the median of all Likelihood images in the input combined.

See citation: <missing>.
